name: Population based
definition: Study done at the population level or among the population groups

name: Disease specific
definition: A study or biobank for which material and information is collected from subjects that have already developed a particular disease.

name: Rare disease
definition: A collection that is focusing on rare diseases

name: Birth cohort
definition: A cohort study for which the subjects are followed from the time of birth usually including information about gestation and follow up.

name: Twin-study
definition: Twin studies measure the contribution of genetics (as opposed to environment) to a given trait or condition of interest.

name: Disease state design
definition: A study design in which the pathological condition of a part, organ, or system of an organism is studied. The etiology may be from infection, genetic defect, or environmental stress.

name: Quality control
definition: A study design where some aspect of the experiment is quality controlled for the purposes of quality assurance.

name: Spontaneous reporting of adverse drug reactions
Combined primary and secondary data collection
No individual level data collected for the purpose of the study
